JOINS:  A MECHANISM TO COMPARE & COMBINE MULTIPLE TABLES
PURPOSE : USED FOR DATA ACCESS & REPORTING

Syntax:
				SELECT <columnlist> FROM  
				TABLE1     			-- LEFT   TABLE
				<JOIN TYPE>
				TABLE2				-- RIGHT   TABLE
				ON <JOIN CONDITION>



TYPES OF JOINS:	

	1. CROSS JOIN	:   USED TO REPORT ALL POSSIBLE COMBINATIONS OF DATA. NO COMPARISONS. 
			    USED FOR FOR UNRELEATED TABLES. Similar to Cartesian Product in Algebra (Maths)
						
	2. INNER JOIN	:   USED TO REPORT MATCHING DATA ONLY.

	3. OUTER JOINS  :   USED TO REPORT MATCHING DATA & MISSING DATA
		3.a - LEFT OUTER JOIN :  All Left Table Data + Matching Right Table Data. 
					 Non match Right table data is reported as null.
								  
		3.b - RIGHT OUTER JOIN :  All Right Table Data + Matching Left Table Data. 
					  Non match Left table data is reported as null. 

		3.c - FULL OUTER JOIN :  Combined output of LEFT OUTER JOIN + RIGHT OUTER JOIN

UNION :  ONE TABLE / RESULT BELOW ANOTHER TABLE/RESULT
JOIN  :	 ONE TABLE / RESULT BESIDE ANOTHER TABLE/RESULT


